 Real Madrid manager Zinedine Zidane is prepared to unleash Eden Hazard in the clash against Chelsea in the Champions League. Hazard joined Real Madrid from Chelsea two seasons ago, his transfer to the Spanish giant has been plaque by injury but this time he is fit and better to face his former side when the stage is set to face the Blues on Tuesday night. Chelsea star rules out of Real Madrid clash in the Champions League Hazard knows that the Real Madrid fans are expecting more from him and it seems the Bernabeu fans are losing their patience with the Belgian star. The attacking midfielder is prepared to take on Chelsea in great form and he aims to send a statement to the Real Madrid faithful. It is left to be seen if Zidane will start Hazard against Chelsea or start Brazilian starlet Vinicius ahead of the former Chelsea maestro. Post Views: 
